<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Read on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/read/</link><description>Recent content in Read on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/read/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Go EOF Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/io-eof-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/io-eof-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="eof--end-of-file-fix"&gt;EOF — End of File Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An EOF (End of File) error occurs when a read operation reaches the end of the data source. In Go, &lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; is returned by &lt;code&gt;Read()&lt;/code&gt; to indicate no more data is available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; is not a true error — it&amp;rsquo;s a signal that the read operation completed successfully but there&amp;rsquo;s no more data. Many Go APIs return &lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; on the final &lt;code&gt;Read()&lt;/code&gt; call. Failing to handle &lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; properly causes programs to treat a normal end-of-data condition as an error.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go EOF Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/io-eof/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/io-eof/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="eof--end-of-file-fix"&gt;EOF — End of File Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An EOF (End of File) error occurs when a read operation reaches the end of the data source. In Go, &lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; is returned by &lt;code&gt;Read()&lt;/code&gt; to indicate no more data is available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; is not a true error — it&amp;rsquo;s a signal that the read operation completed successfully but there&amp;rsquo;s no more data. Many Go APIs return &lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; on the final &lt;code&gt;Read()&lt;/code&gt; call. Failing to handle &lt;code&gt;io.EOF&lt;/code&gt; properly causes programs to treat a normal end-of-data condition as an error.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Kotlin FileNotFoundException — Missing File Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/file-not-found/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/file-not-found/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="filenotfoundexception--missing-file-fix"&gt;FileNotFoundException — Missing File Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;FileNotFoundException&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when trying to access a file that doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist. It&amp;rsquo;s a subclass of &lt;code&gt;IOException&lt;/code&gt; and is one of the most common I/O exceptions in Kotlin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exception occurs when the file path is wrong, the file was deleted, or the path is actually a directory. It can also occur when trying to write to a location where the parent directory doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python IOError — Input/Output Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/ioerror/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/ioerror/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="ioerror--inputoutput-error-fix"&gt;IOError — Input/Output Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;IOError&lt;/code&gt; is an alias for &lt;code&gt;OSError&lt;/code&gt; in Python 3. It was a separate exception in Python 2 for I/O-related errors, but was merged into &lt;code&gt;OSError&lt;/code&gt; for simplification. If you encounter &lt;code&gt;IOError&lt;/code&gt;, it behaves identically to &lt;code&gt;OSError&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Python 2, &lt;code&gt;IOError&lt;/code&gt; handled file and stream operation failures (like file not found, permission denied, disk full), while &lt;code&gt;OSError&lt;/code&gt; handled other system-level errors. Since Python 3.3 (&lt;a href="https://peps.python.org/pep-3151/"&gt;PEP 3151&lt;/a&gt;), these were unified under &lt;code&gt;OSError&lt;/code&gt;. Modern code should catch &lt;code&gt;OSError&lt;/code&gt; or its specific subclasses instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust I/O Error — Input/Output Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/io-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/io-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="io-error--inputoutput-error"&gt;I/O Error — Input/Output Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An error with the message &amp;ldquo;I/O error: &amp;hellip;&amp;rdquo; occurs when a Rust program encounters a problem during input/output operations. This is a broad category covering filesystem, network, and device I/O failures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;std::io::Error&lt;/code&gt; is the general-purpose error type for I/O operations. It wraps OS-level error codes and provides context about what went wrong. The error includes a &lt;code&gt;ErrorKind&lt;/code&gt; enum that classifies the failure (e.g., &lt;code&gt;NotFound&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;PermissionDenied&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;ConnectionRefused&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust I/O Error — Input/Output Failure</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/io-error-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/io-error-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="io-error--inputoutput-failure"&gt;I/O Error — Input/Output Failure&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An error with the message &amp;ldquo;I/O error: &amp;hellip;&amp;rdquo; occurs when a Rust program encounters a problem during input/output operations — filesystem, network, pipes, or devices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;std::io::Error&lt;/code&gt; wraps OS-level error codes with an &lt;code&gt;ErrorKind&lt;/code&gt; enum classifying the failure (&lt;code&gt;NotFound&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;PermissionDenied&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;ConnectionRefused&lt;/code&gt;, etc.). This type is the universal error for all I/O operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;File operations&lt;/strong&gt; — reading, writing, creating files.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Network operations&lt;/strong&gt; — socket reads/writes, connections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pipe operations&lt;/strong&gt; — reading from or writing to pipes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Directory operations&lt;/strong&gt; — listing, creating directories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Standard I/O&lt;/strong&gt; — console operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::fs;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: File not found
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; content &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; fs::read_to_string(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;missing.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Permission denied
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; content &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; fs::read_to_string(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/etc/shadow&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Disk full
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;mut&lt;/span&gt; file &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; fs::File::create(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/full_disk/out.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::io::Write;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;write!&lt;/span&gt;(file, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;data&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Connection refused
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; stream &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std::net::TcpStream::connect(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;localhost:9999&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 5: Broken pipe
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;mut&lt;/span&gt; stdout &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std::io::stdout();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;write!&lt;/span&gt;(stdout, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;data&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-match-on-errorkind"&gt;Fix 1: Match on ErrorKind&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::fs;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::io::{self, ErrorKind};
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;read_file&lt;/span&gt;(path: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;) -&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;io&lt;/span&gt;::Result&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;String&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; fs::read_to_string(path).map_err(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;e&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;match&lt;/span&gt; e.kind() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; ErrorKind::NotFound &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;eprintln!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;File not found: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, path);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; e
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; ErrorKind::PermissionDenied &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;eprintln!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Permission denied: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, path);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; e
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; _ &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;eprintln!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;IO error reading &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, path, e);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; e
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; })
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use--with-custom-error-types"&gt;Fix 2: Use ? with custom error types&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::fs;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::io;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#[derive(Debug)]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;enum&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;AppError&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Io(io::Error),
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Parse(std::num::ParseIntError),
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;impl&lt;/span&gt; From&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;io::Error&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; AppError {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt;(e: &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;io&lt;/span&gt;::Error) -&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Self&lt;/span&gt; { AppError::Io(e) }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;impl&lt;/span&gt; From&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;std::num::ParseIntError&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; AppError {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt;(e: &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;std&lt;/span&gt;::num::ParseIntError) -&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Self&lt;/span&gt; { AppError::Parse(e) }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;read_number&lt;/span&gt;(path: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;) -&amp;gt; Result&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt;, AppError&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; content &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; fs::read_to_string(path)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; num: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; content.trim().parse()&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Ok(num)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-anyhow-for-ergonomic-error-handling"&gt;Fix 3: Use anyhow for ergonomic error handling&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::fs;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;read_config&lt;/span&gt;(path: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;) -&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;anyhow&lt;/span&gt;::Result&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;String&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; content &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; fs::read_to_string(path)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Ok(content)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() -&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;anyhow&lt;/span&gt;::Result&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;()&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; config &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; read_config(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;config.toml&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Config: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; bytes&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, config.len());
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Ok(())
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-retry-on-transient-errors"&gt;Fix 4: Retry on transient errors&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::fs;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::io;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::thread;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::time::Duration;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;read_with_retry&lt;/span&gt;(path: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;, retries: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;u32&lt;/span&gt;) -&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;io&lt;/span&gt;::Result&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;String&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; attempt &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;..&lt;/span&gt;retries {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;match&lt;/span&gt; fs::read_to_string(path) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Ok(content) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; Ok(content),
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Err(e) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; e.kind() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; io::ErrorKind::Interrupted
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; attempt &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; retries &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; thread::sleep(Duration::from_millis(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; (attempt &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;u64&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;continue&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Err(e) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; Err(e),
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;unreachable!&lt;/span&gt;()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::fs;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;match&lt;/span&gt; fs::read_to_string(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;missing.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Ok(content) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, content),
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Err(e) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;eprintln!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;I/O error: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, e),
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Output:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Format / format error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/fortran/format-error2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/fortran/format-error2/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A format error occurs when the format descriptor in a Fortran &lt;code&gt;read&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;write&lt;/code&gt; statement does not match the data type or number of variables being formatted. This includes mismatched data types (e.g., using an integer format descriptor for a real variable), insufficient format descriptors for the number of variables, or malformed format strings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;I&lt;/code&gt; format descriptor for real variables (should use &lt;code&gt;F&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;E&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing fewer format descriptors than variables in the I/O list&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Malformed format strings with incorrect field widths or missing delimiters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;A&lt;/code&gt; format for non-character data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fortran" data-lang="fortran"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! WRONG: Integer format for real variable
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt; format_example
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;implicit&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;none&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;real&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; x
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3.14159&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;write&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;(I10)&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;) x &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! I format is for integers, not reals
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! CORRECT: Use F format for real variables
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt; format_example
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;implicit&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;none&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;real&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; x
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3.14159&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;write&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;(F10.4)&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;) x &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! F10.4 means 10-wide, 4 decimal places
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fortran" data-lang="fortran"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! WRONG: Fewer descriptors than variables
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt; mismatch_example
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;implicit&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;none&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;integer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; a, b, c
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; a &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;; b &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;; c &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;write&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;(I5)&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;) a, b, c &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! only 1 descriptor for 3 variables
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! CORRECT: Match descriptors to variables
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt; mismatch_example
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;implicit&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;none&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;integer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; a, b, c
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; a &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;; b &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;; c &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;write&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;(3I5)&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;) a, b, c &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! 3 descriptors for 3 variables
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fortran" data-lang="fortran"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt; format_error_demo
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;implicit&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;none&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;character&lt;/span&gt;(len&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;20&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; name
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;real&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;value&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;integer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; count
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;test&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;value&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2.5&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; count &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! ERROR: format does not match variable types
